The Egyptian jerboa is a small rodent native to North Africa and the Middle East, particularly Egypt. Recognized for its distinct long hind legs and tail, the jerboa is adapted for jumping and navigating arid desert environments. These nocturnal creatures are renowned for their incredible jumping ability, covering distances up to nine feet in a single leap. To survive in harsh desert conditions, Egyptian jerboas have evolved to obtain water primarily from their food, allowing them to thrive in arid regions where water sources are scarce.
